Hi @terrymanu
I will try it, This is my preliminary idea.
1,Refactoring the constructor of [EncryptDataSource ](https://github.com/apache/incubator-shardingsphere/blob/dev/sharding-jdbc/sharding-jdbc-core/src/main/java/org/apache/shardingsphere/shardingjdbc/jdbc/core/datasource/EncryptDataSource.java) and add java.util.Properties parameters, similar to [MasterSlaveDataSource](https://github.com/apache/incubator-shardingsphere/blob/dev/sharding-jdbc/sharding-jdbc-core/src/main/java/org/apache/shardingsphere/shardingjdbc/jdbc/core/datasource/MasterSlaveDataSource.java);
2,Refactoring the createDataSource method of [EncryptDataSourceFactory ](https://github.com/apache/incubator-shardingsphere/blob/dev/sharding-jdbc/sharding-jdbc-core/src/main/java/org/apache/shardingsphere/shardingjdbc/api/EncryptDataSourceFactory.java) and add java.util. Properties parameters,similar to [MasterSlaveDataSourceFactory](https://github.com/apache/incubator-shardingsphere/blob/dev/sharding-jdbc/sharding-jdbc-core/src/main/java/org/apache/shardingsphere/shardingjdbc/api/MasterSlaveDataSourceFactory.java);
3,Refactoring the constructor of  and add  ShardingProperties parameters;
4,Modify the getSQLUnit method of [EncryptPreparedStatement ](https://github.com/apache/incubator-shardingsphere/blob/dev/sharding-jdbc/sharding-jdbc-core/src/main/java/org/apache/shardingsphere/shardingjdbc/jdbc/core/statement/EncryptPreparedStatement.java) to print the rewritten SQL log according to configuration information;
5,Modify the getRewriteSQL method of [EncryptStatement ](https://github.com/apache/incubator-shardingsphere/blob/dev/sharding-jdbc/sharding-jdbc-core/src/main/java/org/apache/shardingsphere/shardingjdbc/jdbc/core/statement/EncryptStatement.java) to print therewritten SQL log according to configuration information;

Can you modify the codes like this and try again to find any clues?

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/24643893/58691423-7fa42700-83be-11e9-8da6-343b764a42f5.png)

Change to:

```
driver_->connect(host, user, passwd);
conn_->setSchema(m_schema);
conn_->createStatement();
```

The changes are removing the reset() and changing order of setSchema() and createStatement().

